{"TopicId":199551,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Planet discovered in Trinary Star System","CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-12T22:53:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-12T22:53:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/feature/ames/planetary-sleuthing-finds-triple-star-world\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/feature/ames/planetary-sleuthing-finds-triple-star-world\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems like NASA have detected a planet in a Trinary Star System!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1723989402\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/NASA/status/1349122739286716418?s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:505px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-12T22:54:27Z\u0022 title=\u002201/12/2021 10:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 12, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NFUN","CreatedById":78715,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-12T23:23:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs if 2020 weren\u0027t bad enough, we\u0027re about to enter into the Crisis Era. Great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-13T00:12:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTechnically, it orbits one star in a trinary system. Much like Vulcan. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill, very cool! I wonder how its orbit got so inclined.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-13T03:05:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t we already had confirmed planets in the Alpha Centauri system? Which is technically a ternary with Proxima being loosely bound to the AB binary.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-01-15T01:42:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, Proxima has a confirmed planet. This one is in perhaps a more exciting configuration with respect to its suns, though. Here\u0027s a diagram from the article:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022The KOI-5 star system consists of three stars, labeled A, B, and C, in this diagram.\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.24\u0022 width=\u0022985\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/styles/full_width/public/thumbnails/image/koi_5_diagram.jpg?itok=ZWRYi4QC\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe two main suns orbit each other every 30 years, so I\u0027m sure they\u0027re both fairly bright in the planet\u0027s sky.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fact that the planet\u0027s not in planar alignment with the other stars is intriguing and raises the question of how the system\u00A0developed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are probably planets which orbit all three suns in a system like this, but they would be so dim they\u0027d\u00A0be impossible to see with our telescopes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-01-15T01:42:47Z\u0022 title=\u002201/15/2021 01:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 15, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by cubinator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}